title: Citheronia azteca
text:
Citheronia azteca is a <a href="moth">moth</a> of the family <a href="Saturniidae">Saturniidae</a> that lives in <a href="Guatemala">Guatemala</a>, <a href="Belize">Belize</a> and <a href="Mexico">Mexico</a>.
Description.
The species <a href="larva">larva</a>e is <a href="white">white</a> with <a href="black">black</a> spots, while the male moth is <a href="orange%20%28colour%29">orange</a> coloured with white spots and <a href="gray">gray</a> lines.
